<br>
Please don't take this the wrong way but if your guild needs a mage then they need a mage that knows how to play a mage.  Not a mage who knows how to play an enchanter or cleric.  Take a few extra levels(i reccomend from 35 to 45) to not powerlevel and figure out exactly what a Mage can do without being watched over by a chanter and cleric. Let's face it anyone can level from 1 to 65 with the help of a chanter and cleric to watch over them. But to truely know the class, its strengths AND weaknesses) then do not PL every single level.<br>
<br>
Oh and as a general rule which ever Damage Shield has the higher amount of damage it imparts will be the one that stays. a 25 point druid shield won't over write the 45point mage shield and so forth.<br>
