</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mantria>Mantria</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0> at: 1/13/03 9:19:21 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=stehle>stehle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 42<br> <font color=#333333>(1/13/03 9:40:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1779.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: A couple quick questions</span><hr size=1> If you really want to powerlevel your mage, here is how you do it (at least from lvl 10 into the 20s).  Load up every PBAE spells you have an head to Paladul Caverns.<br>
<br>
1-  Cast whatever HP and AC buffs you can on your mage.<br>
2-  Cast highest DS on mage (note: mage can have a pet up, but he won't really need it).<br>
3-  Send someone with high AC (shammy, cleric, warrior, etc) to go round up as many fiends as you can find.  Get a good train of about 30 or so mobs and start heading back to the mage.  It is important that this puller &quot;pulls&quot; the mobs without damage.  I debuff spell works nice.<br>
4-  Pull mobs back to mage and stand there until all of the mobs arrive.<br>
5-  Have mage cast PBAE over and over again.  Eventually he will get aggro and they will start dying on his DS.<br>
6-  Absorb the experience.  On a good pull of 40 or so mobs I would ding from level 11 to 14 in under a minute.  =)  Highly entertaining.<br>
<br>
I definitely agree with the above post, once you get to your 30s, stop and play the mage normally.  Let the skills catch up while learning how to play a mage to its maximum effectiveness.<br>
<br>
Good luck.<br>
<br>
